Name: Description
Child Population by Household Type:
All Household - Population under 18 years in households.
Married Couples - Children who live in married-couple families. 
Single Parents - Children who live in single-parent families. 
Grandparents - Children in households headed by their grandparent.
Other - Children in households for whom relationship to householder is defined as other relative, foster or unrelated child.

Name: Source Notes
Child Population by Household Type: U.S. Census Bureau, American Community Survey 5-Year Estimates, Tables B09002, B09018 (2012-2018); retrieved from https://data.census.gov/.

Name: Notes
Child Population by Household Type: Percentages refer to the population under 18 in households.
